Numerical Differentiation and Integration
This project explores numerical methods for approximating derivatives and definite integrals.
Topics include finite difference formulas, numerical differentiation, error analysis, and numerical integration techniques,
with comparisons of approximation accuracy and convergence.

The Maple source code for each problem is included in this folder. 
The accompanying Project 3 PDF contains both the code and its output, allowing the results to be viewed without downloading or executing the individual files.
